body:
This works beautifully. I was able to use the snippet below and annotate test classes with `@MyCompositeExtension`. It would be nice if users could still use the `@ExtendWith` semantic but this works well too.
``` java
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})
@ExtendWith({
  ExtensionA.class,
  ExtensionB.class,
  ExtensionC.class,
  ExtensionD.class
})
public @interface MyCompositeExtension{}
```

I wasn't able to find this feature in the user guide or javadoc. If the Junit team is interested, I would not mind documenting it. Otherwise, I suppose this issue servers as a form of documentation.

Thanks for your help @marcphilipp
